\section{Results and analysis}
\label{sec:res}

% Describe the survey and population
We collected responses from 282 teachers from Spain and Spanish Speaking countries for the first survey (\textit{survey1} in Fig. \ref{figure:teachers_population}) and 205 for the second one (\textit{survey2}). The sample includes mostly teachers from university, although about 32\% and 8\% are from vocational education in the first and second survey respectively. Regarding gender, 61\% of the teachers were male and 32\% female (approximately 5\% chose not to disclose it). Finally, the responses are equally distributed according to the teaching experience, showing 24\% of responses from teachers with 5 or less years of experience, 26\% for 6-15 years of experience, 30\% for 16-25, and 20\% for teachers with more than 25 years of experience.


